OL,3,CTwo men jailed over 'brutal and
OL,4,Cunnecessary' attack that killed man
OL,6,FCaswell said in his interview that he
OL,7,Fhad not assaulted Mr Shotton and had
OL,8,Ftried to act as a peacemaker.
OL,10,FIn sentencing the two men, His Honour
OL,11,FJudge Robert Linford recognised that
OL,12,Fboth defendants had expressed remorse
OL,13,Ffor their actions on that night but
OL,14,Falso that they had worked together,
OL,15,Fwith Caswell acting "as the muscle".
OL,17,FHe said they had used "appalling,
OL,18,Fneedless violence" in a joint attack
OL,19,Fand that they were both responsible
OL,20,Ffor the death.
